ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yeah if one wants to study basics of Vertex operator algebras, this is a good course for it.
An introduction to the modern theory of vertex operator algebras, recommended.
Summary: vertex operator algebras, starting from the most basic definitions and notions.
It is a fundamental course to the subject and very important for student working in representation theory and lie theory.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I'm not sure if I'll use vertex operator algebra in my research in a near future, but it's very likely that I will.
This class exposed me to new algebraic structures that are relevant in many modern branches of math.
